The paper involves developing and evaluating various multi-agent protocols to train agents to collaborate with teammates in grid soccer, which is a task that falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves multi-agent collaboration, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also involves robotics, as the agents are interacting in a grid soccer environment, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves coordination and communication between agents, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
